import re

def find_numbers(text):
    return re.findall(r'\d+', text)

# Example usage
text_with_numbers = "There are 12 apples and 45 bananas."
numbers_found = find_numbers(text_with_numbers)
print("Numbers found in the text are:", numbers_found)
```

When you run this code, the `find_numbers` function will use a regular expression to find all sequences of digits in the `text_with_numbers`, which are `['12', '45']` in this case. The `re.findall` function returns a list of all non-overlapping matches of the pattern in the string.